title.52: Sgt. Fury and His Howling Commandos Annual (1965) #5

description.0: When Rick and Mar-Vell find out that Dr. Webb is using the tenants of the building in a new psychological experiment, Mar-Vell goes to confront him but is shocked by the heroic behavior of Rick's neighbor.
description.4: By request — the origin of Dr. Doom! (Note: this issue collects stories from Fantastic Four (1961) #1 and Fantastic Four Annual (1963) #2)
description.5: After proposing to Karen Page and promising to retire as Daredevil, Matt Murdock struggles to do just that. Stunt-Master rides into town and tests the grounds of Daredevil's engagement. Will Matt Murdock keep his promise? Or will he find himself suited up once again?
description.6: He's like nothing you've ever seen before- the swamp-born Glob! Hulk takes on his slimiest foe yet!
description.7: After surviving open heart surgery at Municipal Hospital, Tony Stark is abducted once again by Midas. However, this time the golden avenger has an ally in his attempt to escape from Midas' Aegean Island fortress: Madame Masque!
description.9: Odin teleports Thor back to Earth, and his timing couldn't be better! The Thermal Man, a massive robot emitting heat energy, has been terrorizing the streets of New York. Can Thor, alongside Balder and the Warriors Three, save New York from an unexpected heat wave?
description.10: The enslaved Thing must kill...if earth is to survive! Will Ben Grimm comply with his Skrull masters? Even if it means spilling Torgo's blood?
description.11: The Prowler is born! But why is he sneaking into the Daily Bugle? Plus, is Peter's jealousy of Gwen and Flash warranted?
description.12: The Avengers battle a super-powered team in the year 4000 AD. In Egypt, Thor battles a "hero" named Hyperion who comes from Micro-World.
description.13: Captain America and Falcon prepare for their final showdown with the Red Skull. But with the Cosmic Cube in the Red Skull's clutches it seems all hope is lost. Plus, M.O.D.O.K.'s shocking return from the dead!
description.14: Captain Marvel alongside Rick, must face Yon-Rogg once again and his Mandroid robot!
description.16: When Stephen Strange responds to a call for help from an old friend, he certainly never expected to run into a horde of demons!
description.18: The Surfer decides to try to fit into human society once more...
description.19: THE ASSASSINATION OF NICK FURY — by the Hydra agent known as…Bull's Eye!
description.22: The search for Karen Page's father comes to a shocking end! The identity Daredevil has fought to keep secret is finally revealed. Matt Murdock, introduced as the Man Without Fear to the most important woman in his life.
description.23: The green-skinned giant takes on the U.S. army- with Maximus at his back!
description.24: It's an action-packed issue as Midas sends Tony and Madame Masque to break into Stark Industries to capture Tony Stark! Will the Avengers arrive in time to save Tony? Plus: Is Madame Masque having second thoughts about working for Midas?
description.26: Thor, always honorable, is deemed worthy to hear the origin of Galactus. Out of mortal death, comes a rebirth of cosmic energy. The history of Galactus, as told by Galactus, revealed to Marvel readers at long last!
description.27: See the mighty Thing, enslaved on the planet of the Skrulls! Will the Fantastic Four solve the mystery of their missing teammate...before Ben Grimm faces off in a gladiatorial match?
description.28: While the Avengers visit a near-death Tony Stark in the hospital, they are teleported by Kang to a distant realm in 4000 AD.
description.29: With the help of Sam Wilson, the Falcon, Steve Rogers defeats the murderous Exiles. But the Red Skull isn't done yet! Fed up with constant rejection, Rick Jones decides to leave the world of the Avengers and try to find his own way.
description.30: UNCHAINED! Trapped in the Negative Zone, the Supreme Intelligence offers Mar-Vell a way out, but it requires switching places with a young Rick Jones!
description.33: Behind the Ghost exists a much more dangerous foe in control...Mephisto!
description.39: Daredevil goes looking for Karen Page with the intention of proposing. When he finds her, DD comes across an evil ploy! A skeletal creature calling itself Death's Head has kidnapped Karen's father. Daredevil makes a promise to eliminate this threat, but after doing battle with 'Death', his promise seems impossible to keep!
description.40: Once again, the green-skinned rampager must face the murderous might of Maximus and his band of evil Inhumans! If action is your dish, this one's a feast!
description.41: Iron Man's world is crumbling down around him. With Madame Masque bombing Stark Industries and Midas plotting against him, the Iron Avenger is running out of option! Read to find out what happens in the beginning of the end!
description.43: Thor enters the vastness of space as an act of penance for his Warrior Madness. There, Thor is tasked with finding the true origin of Galactus, Devourer of Worlds. Has Odin set an impossible task for his son? And what mysteries will Thor uncover in the universal folds?
description.44: A superhuman Skrull from outer space has landed here on earth. But, he doesn't want to conquer our planet. No, all he wants is...to enslave the Thing!
description.45: After Ultron 6's nuclear bomb fizzles, the robot kidnaps S.H.I.E.L.D scientist Dr. MacLain for his knowledge. Thankfully, Dr. MacLain's brain harbors pacifist beliefs.
description.46: With Captain America away, the Red Skull will play. Captain America is stranded on Exile Island with the Red Skull's murderous minions, while the red-faced devil ruins his reputation with the world. Will the Red Skull finally win?
description.47: Mar-Vell carries out his plan but finds himself part of a plot by Zo (who is really Zarek) and Ronan!
description.48: In his battle with Doctor Strange, Nightmare calls on the help of the JUGGERNAUT!
description.50: The Silver Surfer fights a ghost!
description.51: A day in the life of Nick Fury — but what a day! 'Cause now the hostile hordes of Hydra have joined S.H.I.E.L.D. on the trail of our hard-hitting fugitive! Thrill follows thrill!
description.55: Daredevil's reeling about losing a fight out of fear. The city labels Daredevil a "chicken"! But once DD uncovers a mystery about Mr. Fear, a new foe and explanation for Daredevil's fright is revealed!
description.56: Hulk battles the sensational Sub-Mariner! What more need we say- except to tell you that Stan 'The Man' and 'Happy' Herbie Trimpe bought a dozen each themselves!
description.57: After an epic battle with the Red Ghost, Iron Man and the Unicorn team up to take him down once and for all! But will their efforts be all for nothing, when the Alpha and Beta arrive? Don't miss Iron Man in "Of Mice and Men!"
description.59: Thor accepts his punishment at the hands of Odin following his descent into Warrior Madness. As penance, Thor is forbidden from defending Midgard! What will happen to Earth without a god to defend it? Enter Balder the Brave, the new protector of mortals! But before Balder can say "Yggdrasil", he must fend off the combined evil of Loki and Karnilla!
description.60: The return of the dreaded Skrulls! But this time, it isn't merely earth that's in dire danger- the target for an unmentionable fate is...the unsuspecting Thing!
description.61: The Vision has resurrected Ultron-6, but to what end? Meanwhile, Earth's Mightiest Heroes must save New York City from a nuclear explosion.
description.62: As the ultimate revenge, the Red Skull has used the Cosmic Cube to swap bodies with the Star-Spangled Avenger. Can Steve Rogers convince his fellow Avengers he's not the Red Skull, the crazed genocidal maniac?
description.63: Mar-Vell carries out Zo's plans by stealing a ship and allowing himself to get captured to retrieve an idol!
description.66: It's ALIVE! An ancestor of the original Dr. Frankenstein is about to make a very similar mistake in their present.
description.69: Matt Murdock is no more! Daredevil becomes a permanent identity after Murdock fakes his own death. After teaming up with Spider-Man, our Man Without Fear goes up against...Mr. Fear!
description.70: The Hulk's final confrontation with the Leader! But will Hulk's efforts be enough to avert WWIII? Don't miss this (literally) explosive issue!
description.71: The Unicorn and the Red Ghost in battle again! Will Tony Stark survive them this time around? Find out in this explosive new issue!
description.73: After Adam Warlock takes off with Sif, Thor picks up his hammer and starts swinging! A battle of brawn and rage ensues between two divine beings! Will Thor fully succumb to the ailment Asgardians call "Warrior Madness"? After a previous hiccup, Karnilla recovers her plot to gain Balder's love. What sorcery does Haag have up her sleeve this time?
description.74: The team's happy reunion is soon interrupted by Mole Man! Plus, will Reed and Sue finally settle on a name for Baby Richards?
description.75: The mastermind reveals himself - the oldest of Doctor Strange's foes...Nightmare!
description.77: The secret of the ancient tablet is revealed! The Lizard returns! And a seemingly explosive end for the wall-crawler?!
description.78: Long absent members Iron Man and Thor rejoin the Avengers after personal leave. The team must destroy an Adamantium cylinder created by mad scientist Myron MacLain.
description.79: With the Cosmic Cube back in his grasp, the Red Skull plans to take over the world. But will Captain America fight? Or will he leave the fate of the world in the hands of the next generation of super heroes?
description.80: Nick Fury takes on the zealous terrorist known only as the SUPER-PATRIOT! But nothing can prepare him for seeing the face under the mask…
description.83: Daredevil's retrospective issue. Trapped between the proverbial 'rock and a hard place', Matt Murdock reflects on the events that led to his vigilantism as Daredevil. How does a man remove himself of fear? Daredevil or Matt Murdock must die- but which man?
description.84: The Eve of Annihilation...at the hands of the Leader! More eager than ever to eliminate the Hulk, the Leader builds an android whose only function is to neutralize Bruce Banner. But will the Leader's 'super-humanoid' also usher in WWIII?
description.85: The world of Iron Man is turned upside down when the Night Phantom walks!
description.87: Balder continues to resist the feminine wiles of Karnilla, and the Norn Queen calls in reinforcements. Meet Haag, a morally-dubious sorceress who has mastered the power of persuasion. Will Balder cave to the sinister love of Karnilla? Plus, Thor encounters a strange earthling who goes only by the name of "Him."
description.88: Within the twisted walls of Castle Doom, the team becomes the unwilling participants in Doom's 'power game'. Crystal and Sue are treated to a Latverian banquet...while the men are attacked by flame throwers! The prospect of escape becomes ever bleaker, as the FF fight the machinations of a madman!
description.90: The Human Torch vs. the Sub-Mariner. The only question is, why are these sometimes-allies fighting?
description.91: Surfer zips FASTER than the speed of light to travel into the future! When he goes to investigate future Earth, he soon discovers it's been completely decimated.
description.92: In battle with Man-Mountain Marko, enforcer for the crime boss Silvermane! A rival of Kingpin, Silvermane is looking to secure the same ancient tablet that eluded Wilson Fisk. But will Spidey be able to stop all of these determined criminals?
description.93: The Avengers should consider a new security system! The Swordsman breaks into the Avengers Mansion and discovers that former ally Clint Barton is walking on the right side of the tracks.
description.94: Cap teams up with Rick Jones and Sharon Carter to take down the AIM robot called the Walking Stiletto!
description.95: The Puppet-Master positions Iron Man against Mar-Vell!
description.97: Guest-starring Black Panther! Following an experimental medical treatment, Daredevil is near death. The NYPD and D.A. Nelson have reached out to Panther as a last resort- he must administer an antidote, or Daredevil will die. Black Panther and DD join forces to rescue Karen from the clutches of Starr Saxon!
description.98: The Hulk is trapped at General Ross' Gamma Base! With no escape in sight, and the Leader as persuasive as ever, is this Hulk's stickiest predicament yet?
description.99: The Controller runs amuck, enslaving all in his path, including Tony's new gal, Janice Cord. Can Iron Man save the day? Or will the Controller prove to be too much!

4.text: By request — the origin of Dr. Doom! (Note: this issue collects stories from Fantastic Four (1961) #1 and Fantastic Four Annual (1963) #2)

12.text: The Avengers risk all to halt the spread of the deadly Red Zone bacteria!

15.text: Spider-Man tackles his most fearsome foes, united as the deadly super-villain team The Sinister Six! (this annual collects stories from Amazing Spider-Man Annual #1, Fantastic Four Annual #1, Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #8)

17.text: Introducing the Sting-Ray! Is he Namor's ally, or a deadly new foe?

28.text: The Red Zone spreads, and the body count rises. With some weakened and others imprisoned, can even the Avengers endure?

32.text: Namor and Triton join forces against the sinister Stalker from space!

45.text: The monstrous mastermind behind the Red Zone stands revealed! But who will survive to expose him?

49.text: Namor begins a quest towards his birthplace — only to encounter a menace from the stars!

61.text: The Avengers discover part of the Red Zone's horrible secret, but their own government bars the way to the rest! Meanwhile, a new horror strikes the She-Hulk - at the hands of one of the Avengers' own!

65.text: Namor clashes with the evil TIGER SHARK in "The Sea that Time Forgot!" Featuring an unbelievable landscape!

76.text: Namor returns to Atlantis only to discover a kidnapping plot against Lady Dorma!

78.text: The Red Zone spreads, and not even the Avengers are immune! But as bad as things are, they can always get worse - and it seems that's what the government wants!

93.text: Red mist falls upon the land, and hundreds fall dead. The Red Zone crisis has begun, and it's like nothing the Avengers have ever faced before!
